 Let $p_1$ be the number of free throws Jenny made at the first practice.  Then we know that she made $2p_1$ at the second practice, $2(2p_1)=4p_1$ free throws at the third practice, $2(4p_1)=8p_1$ free throws at the 4th practice, and $2(8p_1)=16p_1$ free throws at the 5th practice.  Since at her fifth practice she made 48 free throws, we have
\begin{align*}
16p_1&=48\\
\Rightarrow \qquad p_1&=48/16=\boxed{3}
\end{align*}
